comments.body:
As additional info: that's how JIB produces the OCI manifest:

Example: (excerpts)

```
    "OCIv1": {
        "created": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
...
History
            {
                "created": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
                "created_by": "jib-gradle-plugin:1.0.0-rc2",
                "author": "Jib",
                "comment": "classes"
            }
...
Docker:

    "Docker": {
        "created": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
...
            {
                "created": "1970-01-01T00:00:00Z",
                "author": "Jib",
                "created_by": "jib-gradle-plugin:1.0.0-rc2",
                "comment": "classes"
            }
```

How buildah produces now:
```
{
    "OCIv1": {
        "created": "1970-01-01T01:00:00+01:00",
     ....
        "history": [
            {
                "created": "1970-01-01T01:00:00+01:00"
            }
        ]
    },
    "Docker": {
        "created": "1970-01-01T01:00:00+01:00",
  ...
        "history": [
            {
                "created": "1970-01-01T01:00:00+01:00"
            }
        ]
    },

```

So this is in line with what JIB does. Just to give some more confidence about being "compliant" in the way we set the reproducible timestamp.
